Troops of the Special Task Force, Operation Safe Haven (OPSH) in Plateau state have rescued two kidnap victims from their abductors. Maj. Ishaku Takwa, the Media Officer of the task force made the disclosure in a statement on Tuesday in Jos. The identities of the rescued victims are Mrs Tabitha Silas, wife of Deputy Chief of Staff, Plateau Government House and Dr Audu Samuel, the Chief Medical Director, Allah Na Kowa Clinic and Maternity, Barkin Ladi. DAILY POST recalls that Tabitha was kidnapped at her residence ‘Little Rayfield close to the Government House in Jos “Silas was also rescued alongside Dr Audu Samuel, the Medical Director Allah Na Kowa Clinic and Maternity Barkin Ladi. “She was kidnapped at her residence in little Rayfield Jos, while Samuel was kidnapped at his residence in Barkin Ladi by the same gang. Takwa added that the victims have been reunited with their families even as he assured to update the media with more details, NAN reports.